<b><FONT face=Arial size=3>Requirements for Vision Membership</FONT></b><p>

<ol><FONT face=Verdana size=1>

<li>Level 47 or higher primary. 
(Existing Vision members with primary characters under level 47 are not affected 
by this policy.)<p></p>

<li>Ownership of Ruins of Kunark.<p></p>

<li>  Ownership of Scars of Velious.<p></p>

<li>Possesion of a Sebilis key before level 52.<p></p>

<li>Possesion of a Howling Stones key before level 55.<p></p></li>

</ol></FONT>


<b><FONT face=Arial size=3>Policy for Key Ownership</FONT></b><p>

<ol><FONT face=Verdana size=1>

<li> Vision members are expected to own 
and keep keys necessary for events.<p></p>

<li> Vision members are expected to own 
and keep keys to others locations (Velious) as the need 
arises.<p></p>

<li> Vision leadership will provide 
events to gather keys when it is more advisable to do so as a 
group.<p>

</FONT></p></LI></OL>

<b><FONT face=Arial size=3>Policy for Guild Sponsored and Planned 
Raids</FONT></b><p>

<ol><FONT face=Verdana size=1>

<li> With regard for multi-class or 
'ALL' items, you will lotto for items you can and will use, provided they are 
not of SIGNIFICANTLY greater value for another class or 
race.<p></p>

<li>   Individual class 
specific items will be handled at the sole discretion of the participating members 
of the affected class as directed by their Class 
Leader.<p></p>

<li> In the case of dispute over item distribution or item lotteries in case (1) or in 
case (2), the guild officer leading the raid will act as the final 
arbiter.<p>

</FONT></p></LI></OL>

<b><FONT face=Arial size=3>Policy for Trading Guild-Gained Items</FONT></b><p>

<ol><FONT face=Verdana size=1>

<li> Although we would prefer that items gained on guild-sponsored raids remain in the guild, 
there are situations where the greater good of the guild is served by making a 
trade. <p></p>

<li> Members trading away guild-gained items will voluntarily allow others to loot before 
them on subsequent drops of items they have traded 
away. <p></p>

<li> Special situations will occur, and they will be handled on an incident-by-incident basis 
in a manner that best benefits the guild as a whole.<p>

</FONT></p></LI></OL>

<b><FONT face=Arial size=3>Policy for Hand-Me-Down Items</FONT></b><p>

<ol><FONT face=Verdana size=1>

<li> Guild members are strongly encouraged, but not required to hand down 'inferior' items when they receive 
guild-gained items.</FONT> 
 <p></p>

<FONT face=Verdana size=1><li> Guild members who receive a guild-gotten item that 
  replaces guild-gotten item, should hand down the 'inferior' guild-gotten 
  item.</FONT>
 <p></p>

<FONT face=Verdana size=1><li> Some members of the guild hand-down items with the provision "hand down this when you are done with it."  It is required that <EM>if</EM> you accept an item given in this manner, that you hand down that item when you receive a better one, whether that be from your own efforts, a guild raid, or another hand-me-down. <p></p>

<FONT face=Verdana size=1><li> Special situations will occur, and they will be handled on an incident-by-incident basis in a manner that best 
benefits the guild as a whole.<p></FONT></p></li></ol>


<b><FONT face=Arial size=3>Hierarchy and Chain of Command</FONT></b><p>

<b><FONT face=Arial size=2>Vision is lead by a council of officers.  The Officer Council is responsible for:</FONT></b><p>
<ol>
<FONT face=Verdana size=1><li> Setting guild policy.<font><p></p></li>
<FONT face=Verdana size=1><li> Keeping the guild working with direction and purpose.<font><p></p></li>
<FONT face=Verdana size=1><li> Planning and organizing raids for the guild as a whole.<font><p></p></li>
<FONT face=Verdana size=1><li> Forming our alliances and managing our relations with other guilds.<font><p></p></li>
<FONT face=Verdana size=1><li> Dealing with disputes unable to be resolved by Class Leaders.<font><p></p></li>
<FONT face=Verdana size=1><li> Selection and management of Class Leaders.<font><p></p></li>
<FONT face=Verdana size=1><li> Assisting Class Leaders with recruitment.<font><p></p></li>
<FONT face=Verdana size=1><li> Dealing with Code of Conduct and Disciplinary issues.<font><p></p></li>
</ol>

<b><FONT face=Arial size=2>A Class Leader represents each individual class and is an officer.  Class Leaders are responsible for:</FONT></b><p>
<ol>
<FONT face=Verdana size=1><li> Planning and organizing raids for specific class items.<br><br>This includes regular items and quest mobs; and may, at the Class Leader's discretion, be mandatory for a particular class.  Class raids that benefit the guild as a whole may also be made mandatory with Council approval.<font><p></p></li>
<FONT face=Verdana size=1><li> The fair distribution of class loot.<br><br>Members of each class will work together with their class leader to determin loot arrangements.  Class leaders may implement any fair or mutually agreeable system that they feel works best for their class.  Officer Council members will assist in a situation where a class is unable to reach a decision.<font><p></p></li>
<FONT face=Verdana size=1><li> Handling recruitment for their specific class.<br><br>The Class Leader will work towards recruiting and keeping a suiable number of like-minded individuals of appropriate levels to make Vision a force in that class.<font><p></p></li>
</ol>

<b><FONT face=Arial size=2>Guild Members are responsible for:</FONT></b><p>
<ol>
<FONT face=Verdana size=1><li> Adhering to the code of conduct for Vision Members.<font><p></p></li>
<FONT face=Verdana size=1><li> Participation in at least one guild event per week (when scheduled) when you are the appropriate level for the event.<br><br>Real life concerns outweigh in-game concerns.  It is acceptable to miss a guild raid because of any signficant real-world event.  It is unacceptable to skip a guild raid because you don't feel as though your class benefits from the raid or because you felt the risk-reward ratio wasn't favorable (e.g. Plane of Sky).<font><p></p></li>
<FONT face=Verdana size=1><li> Vision members are expected to own and keep keys necessary for events.<br><br>These include the keys necessary to meet membership status (Sebilis by level 52, Howling Stones by 55) as well as other locations (Velious) as the need arises.  Vision leadership will provide events to gather keys when it is more advisable to do so as a group.<font><p></p></li>
<FONT face=Verdana size=1><li> Vision Members are expected to own and keep items necessary for events.<br><br> These include (but aren't limited to) resist gear and other encounter-specific items.  Vision leadership will provide events to gather these items when it is more advisable to do so as a group.<font><p></p></li>

</ol>

<b><FONT face=Arial size=3>Code of Conduct for Vision Members</FONT></b><p>

<ol><FONT face=Verdana size=1>

<li><FONT face=Verdana size=1> Participation in all corpse recoveries (group or guild) unless DIRE real-life concerns interfere.</FONT><p></p>

<li><FONT face=Verdana size=1> Polite and civil behavior in /OOC, /SHOUT, /AUC, /G, /GU, /SAY and all other in-game communication.</FONT><p>


<ol>
<li><FONT face=Verdana size=1> Arguments can be handled by /tell, by messages to guild officers to handle 
disputes, and lastly, by /ignore.<font><p></p></li>
</ol>

<p>
<FONT face=Verdana size=1></p>
<li> Be a good sport.</FONT><p>

<p>
<FONT face=Verdana size=1></p>
<li> Be honest.</font><p>

<p>
<FONT face=Verdana size=1></p>
<li> Be fair.</font><p>

<p>
<FONT face=Verdana size=1></p>
<li> Treat your guild brothers and sisters as you would real brothers and sisters.</font><p>

<p></p></LI></OL>


<b><FONT face=Arial size=3>Disciplinary Policy</FONT></b><p>

<ol><FONT face=Verdana size=1>

<li><FONT face=Verdana size=1> While Council Officers reserve the right to remove any member at any time from the guild for any reason, the following list includes a number of (but not all) activities that may cause a Class Leader or Council Officer to issue a <EM>warning</EM> to a Member:</FONT><p></p>

<ol>
<FONT face=Verdana size=1><li> Failure to meet the requirements for Vision Membership.<font><p></p></li>
<FONT face=Verdana size=1><li> Failure to participate in a corpse recovery.<font><p></p></li>
<FONT face=Verdana size=1><li> Failure to attend a mandatory raid.<font><p></p></li>
<FONT face=Verdana size=1><li> Failure to own a key or item needed for a raid.<font><p></p></li>
<FONT face=Verdana size=1><li> Failure to follow officer-given instructions on raids.<font><p></p></li>
<FONT face=Verdana size=1><li> Failure to adhere to teh code of conduct for Vision Members.<font><p></p></li>
<FONT face=Verdana size=1><li> Abuse of the Hand-Me-Down or Guild-Gained-Item policy.<font><p></p></li>
</ol>

<FONT face=Verdana size=1><li> Members issued warnings may be censured in (but not limited to) the following ways:</FONT><p>

<ol>
<FONT face=Verdana size=1><li> Excluded from class or guild raids / events.<font><p></p></li>
<FONT face=Verdana size=1><li> Excluded from class or guild looting.<font><p></p></li>
</ol>

<FONT face=Verdana size=1><li> Members receiving excessive warnings, or in flagrant violation of the Code of Conduct may be asked to leave (or forcibly removed from) the guild.</FONT><p>

<p></p></LI></OL>


												</font>											
